Package jsx.http.event

Event objects and their handlers for HTTP requests.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
OnHTTPAborted Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the HTTPAborted type.
OnHTTPLoaded Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the HTTPLoaded type.
OnHTTPOpen Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the HTTPOpen type.
OnHTTPReceiving Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the HTTPReceiving type.
OnHTTPSent Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the HTTPSent type.
 

Class Summary
HTTPAborted A type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object when the state of its HTTP transmission has been aborted.
HTTPLoaded A type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object when the state of its HTTP transmission has been completed.
HTTPOpen A type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object when the session of its HTTP transmission has just been opened.
HTTPReceiving A type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object when it has just started to be receiving HTTP data.
HTTPSent A type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object when it has just sent a request for receiving data to an opened HTTP session.
HTTPState<T> An abstract type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object to notify a state of HTTP transmission.
 

Package jsx.http.event Description

Event objects and their handlers for HTTP requests.
